President Donald Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Inaugural Reception of the President of Serbia, Aleksandar Vučić, on June 23, 2017. The delegation will be led by Mr. Hoyt Yee, Deputy Assistant Secretary at the U.S. Department of State, and will include the U.S. Ambassador to Serbia, Mr. Kyle Scott, and Mr. Mark Tervakoski, Director for Balkans, Black Sea, and Caucasus Affairs at the National Security Council.